'''Vera Brosgol''' (born August 1984 in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]]) is an [[Eisner Award]] and [[Harvey Award]] winning [[cartoonist]] and a graduate in Classical Animation of [[Sheridan College]] in Canada. She lives in [[Portland, Oregon]] and worked for [[Laika (company)|Laika Entertainment]] where she did [[storyboard]]s and concept art for their [[animation]] productions. Brosgol has also collaborated with [[Shaenon Garrity]] on ''[[L'il Mell and Sergio]]'' for [[Girlamatic]] and drawn several [[guest comic]]s for John Allison's ''[[Scary Go Round]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wordstock Interview: Vera Brosgol |url=https://www.wired.com/geekdad/2011/10/wordstock-interview-vera-brosgol/ |publisher=Wired |accessdate=11 April 2013 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130326040042/http://www.wired.com/geekdad/2011/10/wordstock-interview-vera-brosgol/ |archivedate=March 26, 2013 }}</ref>
