{{infobox organization | name = West Adams Heritage Association | abbreviation = WAHA |image = West_Adams_Heritage_Association_Logo.png |website = {{URL|http://www.westadamsheritage.org/}} |type = Historic Preservation
|location = 2263 S. Harvard Boulevard Los Angeles, CA 90018 |founded = {{Start date |1983|}} in [[Los Angeles]], California |status = nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization
}}
Founded in 1983, the '''West Adams Heritage Association''' (WAHA) is an [[historic preservation]] organization in [[Los Angeles, California]] that is focused on the preservation of the [[Historic West Adams]] section of the city.
As stated on their website: "West Adams is located just south and west of Downtown and contains the city's largest concentration of Victorian and Craftsman homes, five of the city's [[Los Angeles Historic Preservation Overlay Zone]]s, and a concentration of [[Los Angeles Historic-Cultural Monument]]s." [[Image:Frederick_Hastings_Rindge_House,_Los_Angeles.JPG|right|thumb|350px|The Frederick Hastings Rindge House located at 2263 S. Harvard Boulevard.]]
The organization is known for sponsoring neighborhood tours<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1986-11-08/news/vw-28451_1_west-adams|title=The Historic Elegance of West Adams|first=Sam Hall|last=Kaplan|date=8 November 1986|publisher=|via=LA Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://wellingtonsquare.net/tag/waha/|title=waha - Wellington Square|publisher=}}</ref> as well as speaking out about preservation issues affecting West Adams.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-06-07/local/me-168_1_washington-irving-branch|title=Tenant Will Be Sought for Library : Architecture: The Washington Irving branch won't move until someone can be found to take over the historic building.|first=JOHN L.|last=MITCHELL|date=7 June 1991|publisher=|via=LA Times}}</ref>
